		<label>Beholder</label>
    <description>Beholders are dangerous and malevolent creatures, thought to be from another dimension. Their "body" consists of a large magically floating head with a single huge eye. Ten eyestalks sprout from its head, each ending in a single, smaller eye. 
    
If their appearance wasn't bad enough, beholders can shoot magical rays of light from their eyes. These rays can have one of eight effects: paralysis, slowing time dilation, sudden necrosis, telekinesis, forced sleep, petrification, disintegration, and... death.
    
Most of a beholder's body solidifies into a useless stone-like material on death. But the eyestalks remain useful, both as a trophy, and as a potential ritual tool...</description>
